, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth was born about 1383, in Suffolk, England. She had at least 1 son with Henry Sothill. She died on 1 May 1401, at the age of 19."},"et":{"Abt 1383–1 May 1401":"umbes 1383–1. mai 1401","1380–1404":"1380–1404","–1493":"–1493","1383–1401":"1383–1401","1404":"1404","Abt 1383":"umbes 1383","1401":"1401","1 May 1401":"1. mai 1401","1383":"1383","1493":"1493","1380":"1380","Stokerstone, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fi":{"Abt 1383–1 May 1401":"noin 1383–1. toukokuuta 1401","1380–1404":"1380–1404","–1493":"–1493","1383–1401":"1383–1401","1404":"1404","Abt 1383":"noin 1383","1401":"1401","1 May 1401":"1. toukokuuta 1401","1383":"1383","1493":"1493","1380":"1380","Stokerstone, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, England"},"fr":{"Abt 1383–1 May 1401":"environ 1383–1 mai 1401","1380–1404":"1380–1404","–1493":"–1493","1383–1401":"1383–1401","1404":"1404","Abt 1383":"environ 1383","1401":"1401","1 May 1401":"1 mai 1401","1383":"1383","1493":"1493","1380":"1380","Stokerstone, Suffolk, England":"Suffolk, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Elizabeth est née environ 1383, à Suffolk, Angleterre. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Henry Sothill. Elle est décédée le 1 mai 1401, à l’âge de 19 ans."},"de":{"Abt 1383–1 May 1401":"um 1383–1. Mai 1401","1380–1404":"1380–1404","–1493":"–1493","1383–1401":"1383–1401","1404":"1404","Abt 1383":"um 1383","1401":"1401","1 May 1401":"1. Mai 1401","1383":"1383","1493":"1